Welcome to Kai, a simple OpenAI GPT CLI client that lets you ask questions and get answers without leaving the console.

Features:
- Send queries to the OpenAI GPT API directly from the command line
- Pipe outputs from other programs to get answers and insights

API KEY:
Before you can use Kai, you need to set up your OpenAI API key. You can find your API keys at https://platform.openai.com/account/api-keys.

Install
- Mac os homebrew:
     - tap kaspar1ndustries/kai
     - brew install kai
- From source: clone this repo and do `cargo install kai`

Getting started:
- Set up your OpenAI API key in the configuration file at `/Users/<user>/Library/Application Support/rs.kai/config.toml`
- Run Kai with the command `kai <your query>`

